asaccio&rsquo;s Expulsion and ending with Gr&uuml;newald&rsquo;s Resurrection.&rdquo; <br />\n唔知你又有無覺得 John Berger 咁樣講係「吹大咗」?<br />\n<br />\n另外書入面有個章節講到相片嘅故事性 (&ldquo;Stories&rdquo;)<br />\n&ldquo;In one sense, it (the authority of making sense of the stories&rsquo; discontinuities) is invested in nobody and it is nowhere. Rather, the story invests with authority its characters, its listeners&rsquo; past experience and its tellers&rsquo; words. And it is the authority of all these together that makes the action of the story&mdash;what happens in it&mdash;worthy of the action of its being told, and vice versa.&rdquo; 睇到一張相片帶黎嘅感受視乎照片中的角色人物、受眾嘅過往歷練及拍攝者嘅手法。作者應該係按佢自身經歷，同照片中嘅內容有共鳴已而<br />\n<br />\nMaier受傳頌其中嘅原因係佢記錄低其個時代嘅美國<br />\n保留當時嘅人文面貌<br />\n影像內嘅面貌都好難再見<br />\n當然作為外人  我地又能否感受到  又好睇個人的經歷<br />\n<br />\n另外，如果呢篇出現係 The New Yorker 嘅文章有content farm 嘅風格，虛心求教可以係邊度閱覽到有水準嘅攝影評論文章?<br />\n<br />\n唔係太明你最後個段<br />\nVivian Maier影嘅題材都係都市中嘅一般大眾<br />\n佢相對好少拍攝人像model 嘅portrait<br />\n定係你並唔係講緊Vivian Maier?"},{"pid":"3be6e5fdf45f1beb29ed5cb99bf6b448f9aec820","tid":903605,"uid":96708,"like":0,"dislike":2,"score":-2,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2018-11-17T01:35:38.000Z","msg":"有歷史因素加成，是但影都有人吹秦<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/sosad.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /> 當年又真係少女人street photographer 既"},{"pid":"49a3867949edd8161efaaaa033102e9bf9c1564f","tid":903605,"uid":51121,"like":1,"dislike":3,"score":-2,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2018-11-17T02:05:05.000Z","msg":"而家睇番當年計算潮既加埋背景咪有趣<br />\n<br />\n鄭中基啲相夠正la 但佢身份影無咩人會特別講<br />\n反而一個地盤佬影既可以係Facebook 講番一個禮拜"},{"pid":"1df6031777693e15538618113603e0112efc9359","tid":903605,"uid":143582,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2018-11-17T12:17:12.000Z","msg":"做第一代自拍西已經夠上神檯啦，仲話overrated"}]}